                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the Department of State on September
                        28, 1937</hi>
                    <note n="10" type="source" xml:id="d356fn10">Reprinted from Department of State,
                            <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, October 2, 1937 (vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">xvii</hi>, No. 418), p. 268.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1937-09-28">September 28, 1937</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Department of State has been informed by the American Minister to Switzerland
                    of the text of the resolution unanimously adopted on September 27 by the
                    Advisory Committee of the League of Nations on the subject of aerial bombardment
                    by Japanese air forces of open towns in China.</p>
                <p>The American Government, as has been set forth to the Japanese Government
                    repeatedly, and especially in this Government’s note of September 22, holds the
                    view that any general bombing of an extensive area wherein there resides a large
                    populace engaged in peaceful pursuits is unwarranted and contrary to principles
                    of law and of humanity.</p>
            </div>
